  "title": "Part Time Sales Associate",
  "description": "<p>You will act as the first point of contact for clients, bridging the gap between basic inquiries, and complex sales and financial solutions.</p><h3><strong>Job Description</strong></h3><p><strong>1. Client Acquisition & Engagement</strong></p><ul><li><p>Proactively approach potential clients to introduce financial products.</p></li><li><p>Conduct initial needs-discovery to understand a client’s financial goals before referring them to a Senior Director.</p></li><li><p>Handle leads provided and follow up on pending sales applications or interest.</p></li></ul><p><strong>2. Product Advisory & Support</strong></p><ul><li><p>Explain the features and benefits of various financial products in simple terms.</p></li><li><p>Assist clients with applications and onboarding process. </p></li><li><p>Coordinate to ensure client documents are accurately uploaded and processed.</p></li></ul><p><strong>3. Compliance & Administration</strong></p><ul><li><p>Adhere to strict compliance and administration of the company and ensure protocols during every interaction.</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate records of client interactions.</p></li><li><p>Ensure all product materials are up-to-date and compliant with regulatory standards.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Why this role is valuable</strong></h3><p>Working in financial sales in Singapore is one of the fastest ways to build high-level corporate credibility. Even as a part-timer, you gain experience in a highly regulated industry, which is a massive signal of \"trustworthiness\" and \"professionalism\" to future employers in any sector.</p>",
